name: Bellevue
description: Just north of downtown, a mix of high-rise condos and trendy dining and shopping spots, Belltown is a neighborhood where being bored isnít an option.

name: Ballard
description: Just a short drive across Lake Washington, along the longest floating bridge in the world, Bellevue is a green wonderland with nearly 100 parks dotting its landscape between Lake Washington and Lake Sammamish, offering a downtown neighborhood with plenty to do.

name: Belltown
description: This expansive district contains a mix of tree-shaded streets flanked by some of Seattleís loveliest century-old mansions and commercial thoroughfares.

name: Capitol Hill
description: This ìneighborhood of nationsî occupies one of the countryís most diverse zip codes, where descendants from European settlers, East African immigrants, Orthodox Jews, and other cultural groups make for a true melting pot.

name: Downtown
description: As the self-proclaimed ìCenter of the Universe,î this artsy neighborhood on the north shore of the Lake Washington Ship Canal thrives with its bohemian vibe and quirky claims to fame.

name: Lower Queen Anne
description: With bustling bars, restaurants, and attraction-heavy Seattle Center in Lower Queen Anne and historic houses, quaint shopping streets, and quiet parks high up on a hill in Upper Queen Anne, this distinct neighborhood has something for everyone.

name: South Lake Union
description: Surrounding the University of Washington, the University District is an eclectic mix of urban shopping areas; historic homes and architecture; and great cafes, pubs, restaurants, and theaters.
